A woman was near death from a rare form of cancer.  There was one drug
that the doctors thought might save her, a form of radium that a druggist in
the same town had recently discovered.  The druggist was charging $2000--ten
times what it cost to make.  The sick woman's husband went to everyone he knew
to borrow the money, but he could only get about half of what the drug cost.
He told the druggist that his wife was dying and asked him to sell the drug
cheaper or to let him pay later.  But the druggist said, "no."  The husband
became desperate and broke into the druggist's store to steal the drug for his
wife.
